nt with\nseveral predictions and the current evolution of the hemispheric sunspot\nnumbers. The mean apparent width of CMEs and the number of halo CMEs remains at\nrelatively large, constant levels throughout the early phase of SC 25 implying\nthe persistence of weak total pressure in the heliosphere. These results and\nthe perspective of a corona more active than anticipated are extremely\npromising for the forthcoming observations by Solar Orbiter and Parker Solar\nProbe.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 13 May 2022 06:34:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-16"}
