viously assumed. We use the non-detection of a jet axis wiggling to rule out\ncompanions with a mass $>$0.1~\\Msun\\ and orbits between 1~au and 35~au. Any\nobject inferred at these distances using other methods must be a brown dwarf or\nplanet, otherwise it would have impacted the jet axis position. Both the\nprecession and orbital motion scenarios are considered.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 13 May 2022 11:46:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-13"}
