le maintaining the utility loss below\n0.5 Mean Absolute Error (MAE). We also observe that our mechanism is more\neffective in large datasets. For example, with the Swipes dataset, the\ndistinguishability risk is reduced by 60\\% on average while the utility loss is\nbelow 0.5 MAE.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 13 May 2022 13:38:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-16"}
